    "summary": "I use mathematics and computer programming in Python to solve problems that arise in the remote sensing of clouds from space.  I work on a team of scientists to estimate cloud properties from measurements of light scattering.  We work with data measured by laboratory instruments and also air- and space-borne imagers.  My responsibility is to develop algorithms to process these data and determine atmospheric composition. \n\nThese efforts allow us to monitor cloud properties globally on a daily basis --- providing data products that are key components for predicting your local weather next week and the global climate in the coming century.",
